How Gemini & Google Assistant work together

What activity is saved
Your chats, product usage info, feedback, and location info are saved in your Activity (unless the setting is off).

Location info includes the general area based on your IP address, Home or Work addresses in your Google Account, or depending on your Google app permissions, device location. Learn more

How long your activity is saved
If you’re 18 or older, your activity is saved for 18 months, but you can change this to 3 or 36 months or turn Activity off. If it’s off, chats are saved for up to 72 hours to respond to you and help make Gemini secure. Learn more

How your activity is used
If Activity is on, Google uses your activity to improve Google AI with help from trained reviewers. Data reviewed by humans is disconnected from your account and saved for 3 years. Don’t enter things you don’t want reviewed or used. To stop future chats from being reviewed or used to improve Google AI, turn off Activity.

What activity is collected
Google collects your chats and what you share with Gemini (like files, videos, screens, and photos). It also collects transcripts and recordings of your Gemini Live interactions, your feedback, info from websites you visit with Gemini, product usage, and location info (including your device’s general location, IP address, or Home or Work addresses in your Google Account).

If you’re under 18
Your Keep Activity setting is off by default. When it’s off, Google saves your chats for 3 days. It uses them to make Gemini Apps work correctly, help keep them safe, and use your feedback to fix problems. You can turn on Keep Activity to help improve Google AI for everyone.

If you’re 18 or over
Your Keep Activity setting is on by default. When it’s on, your activity is saved in Gemini Apps Activity for 18 months, which you can change to 3 or 36 months. Google uses your activity to develop and improve its services (including Gemini models) as well as to protect Google, its users, and the public with the help of human reviewers. Data reviewed by service providers is disconnected from your account and saved for 3 years. Don’t include info you wouldn’t want reviewed or used. To stop future chats from being used to improve Google AI, turn off Keep Activity.
